value.0: Once a ghostly merchant sought out by adventurers brave enough to endure the perilous trials of the desolate wastes and its forgotten city. It now lingers within the shop as a quiet, diminished echo of what it once was, it drifts between the shelves and counters, staring into nothingness.

A tall, impeccably dressed cambion stands behind the polished counter, a courteous smile resting easily upon his sharp features. His crimson skin is unblemished, his dark horns elegantly groomed, and his tailored coat of black and deep wine silk fits him flawlessly.

Helms such as these have only recently begun to surface in the region, however they look ancient. Relics of an old war, long forgotten and a time nearly lost, these powerful artifacts were likely worn by the champions or paragons of the people that created them.

While the original creators of these helms seem to remain unknown, they do bare an uncanny resemblance to the natives of the Mylock Hills.
